					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No, $2000 isn't the same as $0000 because they result in different chips being enabled. CPU A15-A13 go to the 74LS139 address decoder at U3 in <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File:Neswires.jpg" class="postlink">this schematic</a>, which computes three chip select signals:<br /><ul><li>000: Internal RAM </li><li>001: PPU ports </li><li>100-111: /ROMSEL </li></ul><br />EDIT: corrected</div>

